{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThe E1-verified miss class (epic 6982, §5 of docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md;\nruns/README.md §\"3 MISSED asserted-capability cases\") is: **a plan asserts that an existing,\nNAMED module provides (or lacks) a capability, and the assertion is false against the code** —\nso the executing agent builds on a capability that isn't there, or rebuilds one that already\nis. The three verified misses:\n\n- `dc58` — the plan's sign step used a helper `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` does not have\n  (signing lives in `rebar.signing`; completion.py:350 only *references* the close gate's\n  signing). Pipeline was redesigned mid-flight.\n- `db7b` — the plan proposed bounding the REVIEW_RESULT sidecar via event **compaction**, but\n  by rebar's own contract compaction folds ONLY `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES` (`_commands/compact.py:206`)\n  and REVIEW_RESULT is reducer-ignored, so compaction never absorbs it. Retention is instead a\n  dedicated `sidecar.prune` (`llm/plan_review/sidecar.py:72`).\n- `5886` — the plan proposed a NEW unmapped-Jira-status alert that `fetcher.py` already emits\n  (`_flag_unmapped_statuses` → `fetcher-unmapped-jira-status`, fetcher.py:219). The bug was\n  gate-exempt, so nobody looked.\n\nE4 (assumption/premise verification, blocking) probes assertions broadly but MISSED all three:\nthe named module EXISTS, so E4's existence check passes; the defect is the finer-grained\n**capability-surface** mismatch (module present, specific capability absent — or present when\nthe plan says absent). This story ships a focused probe for exactly that surface.\n\n## What\n\nAdd one new **advisory, code-grounded, AGENT-tier** plan-review criterion, id\n`asserted-capability`, in the G6/E4 rubric family (facet `codebase-grounding`), that fires when\na plan makes a **capability-surface claim about a named module/symbol that it relies on**, and\nthat claim is refuted by the code. Two symmetric directions (one concern — capability claims\nabout named modules must be grounded):\n\n- (A) plan asserts named module M PROVIDES capability C, but M lacks C (dc58, db7b);\n- (B) plan asserts capability C is ABSENT / must be built, but M already provides C (5886).\n\n**Mechanism (grounded against `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/`).** The probe plugs into the EXISTING\ngeneric pass machinery — no core pass change. Pass-1 runs it as one agentic finder\n(`passes.pass1_chunk(..., agentic=True)`, dispatched because its exec tier is `AGENT`;\neval_solver.py:112-113 and pass1.py:3 \"one agent per code-grounding criterion\"). The finder\ngreps/reads the repo (and `resolve_symbol` for installed deps) to confirm the module's actual\ncapability surface. Pass-2 verifier grades its two criterion-local binary sub-answers; Pass-3\ncomputes validity×impact deterministically; Pass-4 coaches surviving advisories. It ships\n**advisory posture (never blocks)** — registry entry `default_posture: \"advisory\"`.\n\n**Registration seam.** Because it is a packaged built-in LLM criterion it must be added to\n`registry.CANONICAL_LLM` (registry.py:79), `CODEBASE_GROUNDED` (:66), and `AGENT_TIER` (:72),\ngiven a routing entry in `criteria_routing.json`, a rubric prompt at\n`reviewers/plan_review_asserted_capability.md`, and a regenerated `## asserted-capability`\nguide section — else `registry.validate_packaged_routing()` (:430) flags it ORPHAN and CI fails\n(the exact failure that bit R2/b080), and `validate_criteria_guide()` (:530) flags a missing\nsection.\n\n**Prior art.** This extends the SAME four-pass finder/verifier/decide/coach machinery already\nused by A1/E4/G6/removal-rationale (see docs/plan-review-gate.md); `removal-rationale` (the\nremoval-side code-grounded advisory dual of A1) is the direct structural precedent for a\ngated-then-grounded two-sub-answer code criterion. No new pass, no new engine construct.\n\n**Effectiveness measurement is future dogfood, not a blocking AC.** The just-landed standing\nrecorder `criterion_effectiveness.py` (commit 0d695be47, d8a5) AUTO-INCLUDES every criterion id\nit sees, so `asserted-capability` accrues `detection_proxy` / `blocking_fp_proxy` from real\nreviews with ZERO per-criterion wiring. The advisory→blocking promotion gate is the protocol\nd8a5 documented in docs/plan-review-gate.md §\"Standing per-criterion effectiveness recorder +\nadvisory→blocking promotion gate\"; this story cites it, it is not gated on accumulation time.\n\n## Scope\n\n- IN: the new criterion (registry + routing + rubric + guide), deterministic unit tests, a\n  committed `criteria eval` fixture set + its result artifact (the bounded sanity check).\n- OUT: promotion to blocking (future dogfood-gated `criteria_routing.json` change per the cited\n  promotion gate); any E2/E3 batch eval (permanently rejected on cost); changing E4/A1.\n- Files: `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/registry.py`, `.../criteria_routing.json`,\n  `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_asserted_capability.md`,\n  `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md` (regenerated),\n  `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/plan-review-asserted-capability.eval.yaml`,\n  `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/asserted_capability_sanity.json`,\n  `tests/unit/test_asserted_capability_criterion.py`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The criterion is REGISTERED advisory and non-orphan. Proof:\n  `python -c \"from rebar.llm.plan_review import registry as r; assert 'asserted-capability' in r.CANONICAL_LLM; assert 'asserted-capability' in r.CODEBASE_GROUNDED and 'asserted-capability' in r.AGENT_TIER; assert r.validate_packaged_routing()==[]; import json; e=json.load(open('src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json'))['asserted-capability']; assert e['default_posture']=='advisory' and e['exec']=='AGENT' and e['facet']=='codebase-grounding'; print('OK')\"`\n  prints `OK`.\n- [ ] The rubric prompt loads and the guide has its section. Proof:\n  `python -c \"from rebar.llm.plan_review import registry as r; assert '## asserted-capability' in open('docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md').read(); print(r.explain_criterion('asserted-capability')[:40])\"`\n  prints a non-empty section head; and `rebar explain asserted-capability` exits 0.\n- [ ] Deterministic unit tests for the non-LLM logic (registration invariants, routing/finding\n  shape, prompt-contract sub-answer keys) pass. Proof:\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_asserted_capability_criterion.py -q` exits 0.\n- [ ] Bounded sanity check committed: a `criteria eval` fixture set with the 3 E1-verified misses\n  (dc58/db7b/5886, reconstructed to their original false-asserting plan text, grounded against\n  current modules) as must-fire and 3 clean plans as must-not-fire. The committed result\n  `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/asserted_capability_sanity.json` shows the probe FIRES\n  on >=2 of 3 misses (report §6 R1 threshold; observed 3/3, stability 1.0) and that any clean-plan\n  fire is ADVISORY (never blocks) and is recorded as the promotion-gate FP signal. Proof: the JSON\n  records `recall_over_misses>=0.66` (observed 1.0), preserves the raw per-case\n  `rebar criteria eval asserted-capability --output json` output, and records\n  `false_accept_over_clean` (observed 0.33 = one advisory false-fire on the no-claim control N1,\n  a non-blocking dogfood datapoint given advisory posture — the exact signal the advisory→blocking\n  promotion gate exists to watch). (6 live single-criterion runs total; NO E2/E3 corpus, NO batch\n  eval.)\n- [ ] The criterion auto-flows into the standing recorder. Proof:\n  `python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/criterion_effectiveness.py --report` (or a\n  targeted unit assertion on `compute_effectiveness`) yields output in which\n  `asserted-capability` appears once it has a firing — verified by a unit test feeding one\n  synthetic firing row through `firings_from_review`/`compute_effectiveness` and asserting the\n  id is auto-included (zero per-criterion wiring).\n- [ ] The advisory→blocking promotion gate is documented and cited: docs/plan-review-gate.md's\n  §\"Standing per-criterion effectiveness recorder + advisory→blocking promotion gate\" (added by\n  d8a5) is the authority; this criterion's rubric/guide state it ships advisory and promotion is\n  a future dogfood-gated `criteria_routing.json` change. Proof: `grep -n \"advisory\" ` on the\n  rubric shows the advisory posture note.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Landed through Gerrit: change carries `LLM-Review +1` AND `Verified +1`\n  and is submitted to main; `make lint && make typecheck && make test` are green on the change.\n  Evidence recorded on this ticket (change number, merge commit, vote outcomes) — verified by\n  attestation, not an in-session repo check."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784415585850175001,"uuid":"443a2915-3ea5-469d-a472-c70f9754e210"}